. induced either their increase in PP and MLN or their decrease in MLN and PP, respectively[
]. Such immunostimulatory effects of the copolymers on Th1 and Th2 responses following the facilitation of uptake of exogenous antigens by APC have been reported[
]. The diversity of the immune cell subsets that could be stimulated by POE-POP in the postweanling pig model system, it suggests that the copolymers when applied as the adjuvant with specific vaccinal immunogen (non-ETEC strain) or alone as an IRM (applied in the current study), may affect either the immunologically commited (T, B and NK-cells) or naïve (CD45RA
) lymphoid cells[
]. Consistent with a former finding of selectively activated CD1
and CD21
gut-residing B cells is our previous finding of stimulated proliferation of IgA
plasma cells and sIgA antibodies by the immunization with POE-POP adjuvanted non-ETEC vaccine candidate strain[
,
]. Also, more recent finding that the copolymer increased proportion of peripheral blood lymphocytes in weaned pigs[
] is in accordance with the highly elevated T (CD4
, CD8
) and B (CD21
) cells observed in this study. As we did not find similar data for pigs we may only quote those found in rodents which suggesting that POE-POP stimulated antibody production, including mucosal antibody responses[
]. However, depending on the quantity of POE in the copolymers they may also stimulate cellular immunity[
]. Recently, the copolymers synthesized using various amonts of POE and POP and with different arrangements of their blocks elicited different immune responses, which were always Th1 specific in mice[
].
